### Data Flow (End-to-End)

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Scene Generator                                             │
│  └─ action_hooks: [intervene_thread, escalate_conflict]     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Scene Narrator                                              │
│  └─ build_choice_prompt(action_hooks) → LLM                 │
│  └─ parse_choices() → choices with action binding           │
│  └─ apply_hooks_to_choices(choices, hooks) → final choices  │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ API Response                                                │
│  └─ choices: [{text, type, action: {type, target_id}}]      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Frontend (rpg.js)                                           │
│  └─ choice.click() → handleRPGInput(choice.action)          │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Simulation Engine                                           │
│  └─ apply_player_action(action.type, action.target_id)      │
│  └─ new_incidents → new_scenes → new_narrative              │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

### Migration Notes

- **Backward compatible**: Existing code that doesn't use `action_hooks` will continue to work
- **Existing choices without `action`**: Will use `"type": "intervene_thread"` as fallback
- **Empty hooks**: `apply_hooks_to_choices` safely handles `len(hooks) < len(choices)`